 spp@bob.eecs.berkeley.edu (Steve Pope) writes:
>honig@ics.uci.edu (David A. Honig) writes:
>
>>> In any case, I recall an NSA employee telling me that
>>> NSA doesn't make use of RSA.
>
>> And you believed him?
>
>Well, I of course don't actually know whether this is true or
>not, nor might he actually know the full truth.  But,
>I haven't seen any evidence to the contrary, and it
>seems quite plausible.
>
>Steve

This is flawed reasoning. "Not seeing evidence" is not evidence
that something doesn't happen (you might not be looking right).

It is plausible that they don't use RSA, but equally (perhaps more) plausable
that they do use RSA, and hide that fact or lie.


Please correct my logic if I misspeak.

